wiki.summary: "Kill It" is a song recorded by the South Korean girl group aespa. It was released October 21st, 2024, as the second track of their fifth mini album, 'Whiplash', under SM Entertainment. Described as a hip-hop dance song with catchy signature synths and gorgeous vocals, expressing a message of warning to those who criticize without a reason with strong raps and vocals, and IMLAY, a DJ and producer of SM Entertainment's dance music label ScreaM Records, participated in the composition and arrangement of the song. Read more on Last.fm.
